The paper proposes an approach for integrating data cleaning into the analysis process, which is relevant to the database (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The approach involves probabilistic repairing of denial constraint violations, which relates to the data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also evaluates the proposed approach using synthetic and real-world workloads, which is relevant to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
